The full equation is E, squared, equals mc squared, squared, plus p times c, squared,

4
00:00:17,670 --> 00:00:22,929
where p represents the momentum of the objectin question. This might all seem a bit confusing,

5
00:00:22,929 --> 00:00:28,859
but in fact you can draw it as a right trianglewith sides E, m c squared, and p times c - and

6
00:00:28,859 --> 00:00:33,329
just use the pythagorean theorem (a squaredplus b squared equals c squared) to give you

7
00:00:33,329 --> 00:00:34,320
the equation.

8
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:38,440
Also, from here it's clear to see that foran object that isn't moving and thus doesn't

9
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:44,719
have any momentum and thus p is zero, we getback our good ole' friend E=mc2. On the other

10
00:00:44,719 --> 00:00:49,719
hand, if the particle in question is massless(like light), then mass is zero and we get

11
00:00:49,719 --> 00:00:54,750
E equals p times c. This tells us that theenergy of a massless particle (like a photon

12
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:58,629
of light) is the same as its momentum (upto a factor of the speed of light).

13
00:00:58,629 --> 00:01:03,399
In fact, the closer the energy of somethingis to p times c, the closer that something

14
00:01:03,399 --> 00:01:07,950
is to behaving like light (I mean, look here,this tiny little bit of mass is hardly mass

15
00:01:07,950 --> 00:01:08,860
